sentences.sContent: The militia in Lebanon has agreed to pull out of Beirut.
sentences.sCn: 黎巴嫩的民兵组织已经同意撤出贝鲁特。

sentences.sContent: Economic sanctions will be lifted once two-thirds of their forces have pulled out.
sentences.sCn: 一旦他们的部队撤出2/3，经济制裁就会解除。

synos.tran: 离开，撤离；拔出；渡过难关；恢复健康；折叠的大张插页；飞机进场重新飞起

trans.tranOther: If troops pull out of a place or if their leader pulls them out, they leave it
